=Bio=

Benjamin Tincq is an entrepreneur and peer-to-peer strategist. His work is focused on the rise of p2p models and the collaborative economy. I research how the distributed structure of the internet replicates in real-life organizations, and how this is disrupting consumption, production, finance, education, work, politics, and every aspect of our lives.

He is a co-founder of [[Ouishare]].net, an open global community of passionate people (entrepreneurs, designers, makers, researchers, politicians, citizens and many more) working to accelerate the shift toward this emerging collaborative economy. We explore, connect and promote the ideas and projects, which we believe can bring upon huge societal benefits through sharing, collaboration and openness.

